 of thinkers sheds new light on the emergence of the concept of consciousness and the significance of human natality to central questions in the fields of literature, philosophy, and the history of science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aConsciousness in literature. 0aEnglish poetryy17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aExperience in literature. 0aFetus in literature. 0aInfant psychologyzEnglandxHistoryy17th century. 0aPhilosophy, Englishy17th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aJohn Locke.  aJohn Milton.  aRené Descartes.  aThomas Traherne.  aconsciousness.  aembryology.  anatality.  aphilosophy.  apoetry.  atheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106930960 cprintz978022672509340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226725260423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226725260/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070474-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020